{meta: artist The Easter Brothers}
{meta: composer Edd Easter, James Easter, and Russell Lee Easter}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]I'll have a heart that will [D7]never break [G]again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]I remember standing at my daddy’s [G]bedside
[D7]And the tears filled up the wrinkles on his face
[G]As I held his withered [C]hand he smiled and [G]whispered
[D7]Son I’m going to live in a better [G]place
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]And I’ll have eyes that will never fill with teardrops
[G]I’ll have legs that will never ache with [D7]pain
[G]I’ll have hands that will never age and [C]wither
[G]And a heart that will [D7]never break [G]again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]I have often heard and read about that [G]city
[D7]Where with Jesus we shall live for ever more
[G]There are mansions [C]in construction for my [G]dwelling
[D7]And the streets of gold will run by my front [G]door
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[C]All the eyes of the blind will than be [G]open
[D7]And they’ll join the victory march with the lame
[G]And the deaf who’s never [C]heard the roar of [G]thunder
[D7]Will rejoice to hear the Savior call his [G]name
{end_of_verse}

